  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2011-02-08", 
    "text": "Consumer Protection Act of 2011 - Invalidates as a defense to a tort claim in any court in the United States that a manufacturer of a product has fulfilled that manufacturer's duty of care when providing all of the necessary information to a learned intermediary, who then interacts with the consumer of the product. Defines a \"learned intermediary\" as a person licensed under applicable state or federal law to advise a consumer whether or not to use the product in question."
  }, 
